<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Portfolio of Student</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<style>
    .intro ul.techstack {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 20px;
    max-height: none;
    overflow: visible;
    display: block;
}

.intro ul.techstack li {
    background: none;
    border-left: none;
    padding: 2px 0;
    color:beige;
}
</style>

<body>

    <%- include('partials/navbar') %>
        <div class="menu">
            <div class="intro">
                <h1>I am Me</h1>
                <p>A simple portfolio website with <b>CSS</b> & <b>HTML</b>> now uses <strong>server-side rendering
                        (EJS)</strong>
                    to dynamically inject backend data into HTML before sending it to the browser.</p>

                <p style="margin-bottom: 1%; font-weight: bold;">Techstack:</p>
                <ul class="techstack">
                    <li>Node.js + Express</li>
                    <li>MongoDB (visitor data storage)</li>
                    <li>Docker (containerized app + database for consistent local setup)</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top: 2%; color:bisque;">Mongo Express is used during development to inspect the database directly.</p>

                <h2>Visitors so far:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <% if (data && data.length> 0) { %>
                        <% data.forEach(user=> { %>
                            <li>
                                <strong>
                                    <%= user.name %>
                                </strong> - <%= user.email %>
                                    <p>
                                        <%= user.message %>
                                    </p>
                                    <small>Submitted: <%= user.createdAt %></small>
                            </li>
                            <% }) %>
                </ul>
                <% } else { %>
                    <li>No visitors yet.</li>
                    <% } %>

            </div>
        </div>

</body>

</html>